all ingredients in cryoprotective soluti: 50 mg/ml P1 (PEG−PA; 5000−500) in DMEM
cooling rate: -1 ◦C/min to −80 ◦C then transferred to liquid nitrogen at -196°C
comments about method: PEG−PA block copolymers were synthesized via the ring-opening polymerization of N-carboxy anhydrides of L-alanine initiated by α-amino-ω-methoxy PEG. Post thaw, the cells were counted using trypan blue staining.  The cell recovery values at 24 h after plating were calculated by multiplying cell recovery after thawing and optical density at 450 nm at 24 h after plating
comments about results: the PEG−PA (5000−500) block copolymer is suggested to be a promising antifreezing cryoprotectant for stem cells
